<h1> Gracie Abrams </h1>

<div class="leadGraph"> 
<p>
Abrams, born in 1999 to filmmaker J.J. Abrams and producer Katie McGrath, is a young artist known for her intimate, raw pop music. She began building her career about five years ago with EPs such as “Minor” and “This Is What It Feels Like,” followed by her debut studio album “Good Riddance” in 2023. After opening for Taylor Swift on the Eras Tour, Abrams gained recognition from a global audience. Her second studio album, “The Secret of Us,” released in 2024, marked her breakthrough as an artist. The album debuted at <a href="fanpage2.html" target="_blank">No. 1 on Billboard’s Top Album Sales chart</a>, selling about 50,000 copies in the United States in its first week. The album’s success, along with its later deluxe release, further cemented Abrams as one of pop music’s fastest-rising artists.
</p>
